      "patchset_number": 9,
      "line": 79,
      "message": "See the code in org.onap.cps.ncmp.impl.data.DmiDataOperations#getDistinctCmHandleIds which is used in legacy batch data operation:\n\n    private Set<String> getDistinctCmHandleIds(final DataOperationRequest dataOperationRequest) {\n        return dataOperationRequest.getDataOperationDefinitions().stream()\n                .flatMap(it -> it.getCmHandleReferences().stream())\n                .map(alternateIdMatcher::getCmHandleId)\n                .collect(Collectors.toSet());\n    }\n\nIt needs to be updated to ignore the CmHandleNotFoundException.\nEven better, it could use batch lookups with IMap.getAll(keys):\n\n    private Set<String> getDistinctCmHandleIds(final DataOperationRequest dataOperationRequest) {\n        final Set<String> cmHandleReferences = dataOperationRequest.getDataOperationDefinitions().stream()\n                .flatMap(it -> it.getCmHandleReferences().stream())\n                .collect(Collectors.toSet());\n        return cmHandleIdPerAlternateId.getAll(cmHandleReferences).values();\n    }",
      "author": {
